## Conlanging
In addition to my academic interest in linguistics are the activities related to linguistics I do in my free time. One of these is conlanging, the hobby that helped spark my interest in language.

Conlangs, short for constructed languages, are languages that are consciously made for some purpose, as opposed to natural languages (natlangs) that arise more spontaneously. I have been conlanging since I was 13, though my first conlangs were basically relexifications (relexes) of English.
